<br>
Overview <br>
<br>
The Savage is shaping up to be a solid, balanced, fun class. There are a few areas that may be a little too strong, but there are also areas that are desperately in need of enhancement. Most noteably, nothing has been done to assist with PvE downtime while there are a few items in the RvR arena that need to be watched closely. <br>
<br>
<br>
Concerns <br>
<br>
The Savage struggles with long downtime in the solo PvE world, while conversely excels in the RvR world. The first concern is that downtime is too long in solo PvE; this is a result of needing to use our buffs to kill our prey which results in extra damage after a fight. The second concern is that Savages may be gaining too much benefit from the hybrid spec joining axe/sword/hammer with the HTH double/triple/quads. There are no other major concerns that are not bugs. <br>
<br>
<br>
Specline Issues <br>
<br>
Axe/Sword/Hammer &amp; HTH hybrid Savages may do too much damage. This may be a result of combining full tank Weapskill weaponry with the ability to double/triple/quadruple hit, along with the Haste/DPS advantages of Savagery. I would suggest simply placing all Savage weaponry on the same WeapSkill table as HTH. <br>
<br>
When Savagery abilities are used in PvE, the resultant downtime is far greater than that of most other classes. As a counter to this, I suggest an ability called Kelgor's Recovery. This ability would be non-combat, focus-only and would regenerate Health at an accelerated rate at the cost of Endurance. <br>
<br>
Multi-target styles in the HTH line are basically useless in RvR. There is little-to-no opportunity to use them with their miniscule range and lack of real additional damage. We need to look at ways of enhancing the multi-target aspect of the HTH styles without overpowering the attacks. <br>
<br>
Ravager, the Savage unique RA, is broken and useless. It's printout is that of Void, and does unimpressive damage. In it's place, I suggest an ability called Sense Aggression. This ability would be a focus-ability in which the Savage would trade a steady HP loss for the ability to have True-Sight in a 300WU radius around himself (with attached animation). <br>
<br>
Insta-taunt does not need to interrupt casting/archery. This was a side-effect of the ability, and not a reason the ability was requested. I requested the insta-taunt as a means to control aggro and pull mobs in PvE. <br>
<br>
<br>
New Issues <br>
<br>
There are no additional new issues as a result of 1.62 that I am yet aware of. <br>
<br>
<br>
Other Issues <br>
<br>
- Prevent Flight is missing from the Savage RA list. <br>
- Necromancer pets are not affected by multi-target styles. <br>
- Savages have the Small Shields ability listed, but cannot equip shields of any kind. <br>
- There are no style trails when wearing greave HTH weaponry. <br>
- Damage Adds may be too powerful when combined with quadruple or triple hits. <br>
<br>
<br>
Item Problems <br>
<br>
Savage HTH Quest Rewards are Inferior - When performing quests, Savages are finding the the HTH weapon rewards they receive are inferior to their axe counterparts. <br>
<br>
